{
  "_comment": [
    "iTerm2 Dynamic Profile for screencast / Recordly recordings.",
    "Lives inside the iterm_for_recordly/ folder alongside its AppleScript.",
    "Symlinked into ~/Library/Application Support/iTerm2/DynamicProfiles/ so iTerm2 auto-loads it.",
    "Edit this file at its real location, not via the symlink.",
    "Edits to this file are picked up live by iTerm2 (no restart needed).",
    "",
    "Launched via iterm_for_recordly.applescript, which opens a window using this profile",
    "named 'Recording' at a fixed position and runs zsh with a minimal PROMPT.",
    "",
    "Colour scheme: FunForrest (warm autumn palette). To swap to Retro, replace the color",
    "blocks below with values from /Users/j/Downloads/iterm_themes/Retro.itermcolors.",
    "Note: Retro collapses all ANSI colours to a single green; only use it when you will NOT",
    "be showing colourised output (ls, git diff, etc.)."
  ],
